Source: linux-uki
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Maintainer: skosachiov <skosachiov@gmail.com>
Uploaders: skosachiov <skosachiov@gmail.com>
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat,
	       sbsigntool,
	       openssl

Package: linux-uki-unsigned
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Multi-Arch: same
Description: Unified Kernel Image for booting Linux under Secure Boot
 This package provides unsigned Unified Kernel Images (UKI) that combine
 kernel, initramfs, and boot parameters into a single executable UEFI image.
 UKIs simplify the boot process and provide better integration with UEFI
 Secure Boot environments.

Package: linux-uki-helpers-amd64-signed-template
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
Description: Template for signed AMD64 Unified Kernel Images
 This package contains template files for generating signed AMD64 Unified
 Kernel Images. These templates are used during the Secure Boot signing
 process to create production-ready UKIs for AMD64 systems.

Package: linux-uki-helpers-arm64-signed-template
Architecture: arm64
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
Description: Template for signed ARM64 Unified Kernel Images
 This package contains template files for generating signed ARM64 Unified
 Kernel Images. These templates are used during the Secure Boot signing
 process to create production-ready UKIs for ARM64 systems.
